---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Singapore Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/singapore/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Malaysia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/malaysia' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Japan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/japan' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'singaporeFit', header: 'Singapore Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$480-650/mo', singaporeFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$550-750/mo', singaporeFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$420-580/mo', singaporeFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$400-560/mo', singaporeFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AIA Singapore', entryAge: '70', renewal: '99', monthlyFrom: 'S$400-800/mo', singaporeFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$420-650', annual: '$5,040-7,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$580-850', annual: '$6,960-10,200' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$780-1,150', annual: '$9,360-13,800' },
  { category: 'Singapore IP (Integrated Shield)', monthly: 'S$300-600', annual: 'S$3,600-7,200' },
  { category: 'MediShield Life (Mandatory)', monthly: 'Age-based', annual: 'S$300-1,530 (65-90)' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Singapore 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Singapore. World-class hospitals, MediShield Life, visa options, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Singapore"
  subheadline="Singapore offers world-class healthcare in English, exceptional safety, and first-world infrastructure—but premium costs to match."
  heroImage="/images/countries/singapore-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Singapore</h2>
  <p>
    Singapore is consistently ranked as one of the best places to live in Asia. For seniors, it offers exceptional healthcare (ranked #2 globally), English as an official language, extremely low crime, efficient infrastructure, and a clean, modern environment.
  </p>

  <p>
    The city-state is compact and highly accessible. Public transport is excellent. Hospitals are world-class with no language barriers. The expat community is large and established, with plenty of social activities for retirees.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> World-class; ranked #2 globally</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English is official; widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> S$4,000-7,000/month ($3,000-5,200) for comfortable living</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> One of the safest cities globally</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; year-round 25-32°C with high humidity</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No capital gains tax; favorable tax treatment for retirees</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Singapore's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Singapore's healthcare system combines public and private options. Public hospitals (restructured hospitals) offer excellent care at subsidized rates for residents. Private hospitals like Mount Elizabeth, Gleneagles, and Raffles Hospital provide premium care with shorter waits.
  </p>

  <p>
    All Singapore residents are covered by MediShield Life, a basic catastrophic health insurance. Most add an Integrated Shield Plan (IP) for enhanced coverage including private hospital access. Medisave (mandatory health savings) helps fund premiums and co-pays.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Cost Warning</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Singapore healthcare is excellent but expensive. A private hospital stay can cost S$1,000-2,000+ per night. Without proper insurance, medical bills can be substantial. Comprehensive international insurance or enhanced local coverage is essential.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Singapore's immigration policy favors working professionals and investors. Options for retirees include:
  </p>

  <h3>Global Investor Programme (GIP)</h3>
  <p>
    Requires S$10M+ investment in a Singapore business or fund. Provides Permanent Residency for successful applicants.
  </p>

  <h3>Employment Pass (EP) → PR</h3>
  <p>
    Some retirees establish consultancies or advisory roles. After 2-3 years on EP, you can apply for Permanent Residency.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-Term Visit Pass (LTVP)</h3>
  <p>
    Available to spouses of Singapore citizens/PRs. Also available in special circumstances for retirees with strong Singapore connections.
  </p>

  <h3>Malaysia as Base</h3>
  <p>
    Many retirees live in nearby Johor Bahru, Malaysia (20 minutes from Singapore) with MM2H visa, and visit Singapore regularly for healthcare and amenities.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements depend on your residency status:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Permanent Residents:</strong> Mandatory MediShield Life enrollment; can add IP</li>
    <li><strong>Employment Pass holders:</strong> Must maintain comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Visitors/LTVP:</strong> International insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Medical tourists:</strong> Recommend travel insurance with high limits</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Singapore</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Given Singapore's high healthcare costs, comprehensive international insurance is essential for non-residents. PRs should supplement MediShield Life with an Integrated Shield Plan. Consider evacuation coverage to Malaysia or Thailand for non-emergency procedures at lower cost.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Singapore, these providers offer strong coverage for one of Asia's most expensive healthcare markets:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Singapore</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Excellent Singapore hospital network, direct billing at major private hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), strong direct billing</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good value, strong regional coverage</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> Competitive Singapore pricing</li>
    <li><strong>AIA Singapore:</strong> Local option for PRs, integrates with MediShield Life</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Singapore.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Singapore is one of the most expensive places for health insurance due to high local healthcare costs:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> A S$5,000+ deductible can significantly reduce premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Exclude US/Canada if not needed</li>
    <li><strong>Public hospital option:</strong> Accepting public hospital care reduces premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Malaysia backup:</strong> Consider Johor Bahru hospitals for non-emergency care (much cheaper)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British PR, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Long-term Singapore resident with PR status. Has MediShield Life but wants enhanced coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Add AIA Integrated Shield Plan for private hospital access. Keep Cigna Global for travel and UK visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> IP ~S$500/month + Cigna (Singapore excluded) ~$250/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Retiree, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving to Singapore on LTVP (spouse is Singaporean). Needs comprehensive coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global Lifeline plan. Direct billing at Mount Elizabeth, Gleneagles.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$800/month. After PR approval, can add MediShield Life.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Johor-Singapore Lifestyle, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Living in Johor Bahru, Malaysia. Uses Singapore for healthcare and shopping.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> MM2H visa for Malaysia. Allianz Care covering both countries.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$450/month. Lower Malaysia living costs offset insurance premium.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to Singapore without significant wealth?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Singapore's immigration policy makes pure retirement difficult without wealth or employment. The GIP requires S$10M+ investment. Many moderate-income retirees base themselves in nearby Malaysia (Johor Bahru) and visit Singapore regularly. This provides both countries' benefits at lower cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How expensive is healthcare in Singapore?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very expensive by regional standards. A private hospital room costs S$500-2,000/night. Major surgery can cost S$50,000-100,000+. Public hospitals are subsidized for residents but still costly. Comprehensive insurance is essential—going without is a significant financial risk.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the heat and humidity?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Singapore is tropical year-round: 25-32°C with 80-90% humidity. Air conditioning is ubiquitous. Many seniors adapt well, but some find the constant heat challenging. Indoor activities, malls, and air-conditioned transport make it manageable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Singapore good for seniors with mobility issues?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent. Singapore is highly accessible with wheelchair-friendly MRT (subway), buses, and buildings. Most malls, hospitals, and public spaces have good accessibility features. The flat terrain (no hills) makes getting around easier than many cities.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Singapore.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Singapore authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
